news.title: Delhi civic body launches C&D waste removal drive to tackle winter pollution
news.para: A meeting was held a few days back and it was decided that a special drive will be launched to ensure that deputy and assistant commissioners conduct daily inspections in Delhi's 12 zones, Oberoi said.

news.title: Jaipur development body demolishes seven illegal colonies
news.para: Officials said that the first colony was being developed on around two bighas of private agricultural land in the Vatika village on Neemdi Road. The second colony was being established on an eight bigha private agricultural land in Simliya village.

news.title: Kerala government plans 1,000 homes under Wayanad township project
news.para: The plan is to build around 1,000 houses across two townships. Short-term quotations for conducting a detailed total station survey of the proposed land will be invited soon. The projects will be executed using the engineering, procurement, and construction (EPC) model.

news.title: Paying guest owners seek relaxation in Bengaluru civic body's guidelines
news.para: To create awareness in the fraternity about the guidelines, PG Owners' Association has decided to hold a meeting on Oct 15 at Vijayanagar. At the same time, the association is hoping BBMP will announce revised guidelines at the meeting. BBMP sources said they will release the changed guidelines soon.

news.title: Delhi: DDA seeks approvals for 498 EWS flats at Karkardooma TOD project
news.para: The whole complex is being developed by the National Building Construction Corporation (NBCC). Although work at the site was completed in July, DDA will take over the possession of the flats after completing its inspection and fulfilling other formalities.

news.title: Signature Global registers pre-sales of Rs 27.8 billion in Q2 FY25
news.para: Signature Global registered pre-sales of Rs 59.0 billion in H1 FY25, a 217% year-on-year growth. With this, it claims to have already achieved 59% of its sales guidance of Rs 100 billion for FY25.

news.title: Sobha reports 32% decline in sales bookings to Rs 1,178.5 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: In a regulatory filing on Monday, Bengaluru-based Sobha Ltd informed that its sale bookings stood at Rs 1,178.5 crore in the second quarter of this fiscal as against Rs 1,723.8 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Maharashtra: 150 housing societies receive cooperative bank loans for self-redevelopment
news.para: "The loans will now benefit the housing societies," state commissioner of cooperation and registrar of cooperative housing societies Deepak Taware said on Thursday.

news.title: Garuda Construction IPO subscribed 1.9 times on October 8
news.para: The initial share sale received bids for 3,80,15,666 shares against 1,99,04,862 shares on offer, according to data available with the NSE.

news.title: Noida authority to refer developers owing Rs 1,035 crore to EOW for investigation
news.para: On Tuesday, the Authority send the developers a final notice seeking details on unsold flats and shops, and unutilised sections of the project land. The cases will be referred to EOW if the data is not shared soon, officials said.

news.title: Lucknow: ED files prosecution complaint against Shine City group in PMLA case
news.para: The ED has initiated the investigation based on approximately 554 FIRs registered by Uttar Pradesh police against Naseem and Shine City Group for allegedly collecting an amount to the tune of Rs 1000 crore from the public in the name of investment, that will give them huge returns.

news.title: Outlook stable for real estate this fiscal
news.para: Residential supply to match demand; leasing momentum in commercial space to continue

news.title: IndoSpace plans to invest Rs 4,500 crore in logistics and warehouse parks in Tamil Nadu
news.para: IndoSpace's total equity committed to the state as on date stands at USD 380 million, and the facilities offer a potential chargeable area of 15.4 million sq ft.

news.title: CBRE to manage NetApp's 1.07 million sq ft office spaces
news.para: The portfolio consists of NetApp’s campus in Bengaluru and sales offices in Bengaluru, Mumbai and New Delhi.

news.title: PE investment in real estate touch $3.9 billion in January-September 2024: Report
news.para: The PE inflows were at $2.2 billion (Rs 186 billion) in Q3 2024. The inflows were $6.7 billion in 2019, $6.6 billion in 2020, $3.4 billion in 2021, $3.4 billion in 2022, and $3.9 billion in 2023.

news.title: Ashiana Housing's sales bookings touch Rs 673 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: In a regulatory filing on Tuesday, Ashiana Housing reported that its sales bookings stood at Rs 673.05 crore in the second quarter of this fiscal as against Rs 325.60 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Keystone Realtors sales bookings surge to Rs 700 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Keystone Realtors reported pre-sales of Rs 700 crore in the second quarter of the 2024-25 fiscal as compared to Rs 306 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Telangana government reveals 171 water bodies within ORR lost in 10 years
news.para: ​​Though the lakes were spread over 3,586.12 acres in 2014, when the new state was formed, squatters have encroached upon over 386 acres, worth several thousands of crores.

news.title: Manual khata remains relevant: Tushar Giri Nath, BBMP chief
news.para: In an interview, the Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP) Chief Commissioner Tushar Giri Nath discusses the current efforts, future plans, and actions being taken to address these issues and improve conditions for the city’s residents.

news.title: TIDCO to allot land parcels in Sulur from next month
news.para: TIDCO plans to allot parcels of land to various companies to set up their manufacturing units at the Aerospace and Defence (A&D) Park at Varapatti in Sulur taluk in the district from next month.
